From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 19:12:02 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] ui/build: allow perl in the path sandbox

The inline Linux 4.9 kernel build (kernel/motorola/sdm632 graft) invokes perl
(lib/build_OID_registry, timeconst.pl, ...). Stock AOSP's path allowlist omits
perl, so the sandboxed build errors on first use. LineageOS allows it for
kernel builds.

---
 ui/build/paths/config.go | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/ui/build/paths/config.go b/ui/build/paths/config.go
index 110ddee894ad..01f0a448a792 100644
--- a/ui/build/paths/config.go
+++ b/ui/build/paths/config.go
@@ -101,6 +101,11 @@ var Configuration = map[string]PathConfig{
 	"javap":       Allowed,
 	"lsof":        Allowed,
 	"openssl":     Allowed,
+	// perl is required by the inline kernel build (e.g. lib/build_OID_registry
+	// generating lib/oid_registry_data.c, timeconst.pl, etc.) for the
+	// kernel/motorola/sdm632 4.9 source graft. Not in stock AOSP's allowlist
+	// (falls to Missing -> errors on use); LineageOS allows it for kernel builds.
+	"perl":        Allowed,
 	"pstree":      Allowed,
 	"rsync":       Allowed,
 	"sh":          Allowed,
